 Sunday World has learnt that the Northern Gauteng High Court has granted FNB an order to attach Vilakazi's Norkem Park house in Kempton Park, East Rand, after he failed to keep up with monthly instalments.Vilakazi, who bought the house jointly with Constance Lebogang Vilakazi, feigned surprise when we asked him about the matter."What are you talking about? Who is Constance? I don't know who that is. The amount I was owing which was about R15 000 was settled in June last year," he said.The retired player, who also played for AmaZulu, Ajax Cape Town and Free State Stars, said he did not know why the bank applied for an attachment order in November last year.TO READ THE FULL STORY GET A COPY OF TODAY'S SUNDAY WORLD AT YOUR NEAREST STORE 